<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Expired on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/expired/</link><description>Recent content in Expired on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/expired/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C Certificate has expired</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/certificate-expired/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/certificate-expired/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="certificate-has-expired"&gt;Certificate has expired&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An expired certificate means the X.509 certificate&amp;rsquo;s validity period has passed. SSL/TLS libraries will reject connections using expired certificates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Server certificate expired
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Certificate not renewed before expiry
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: System clock wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Clock set to wrong date
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Certificate authority expired
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Intermediate CA certificate expired
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-renew-the-certificate"&gt;Fix 1: Renew the certificate&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Let&amp;#39;s Encrypt&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;certbot renew
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Self-signed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;openssl x509 -in old.pem -out new.pem -days &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;365&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-system-clock"&gt;Fix 2: Check system clock&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;date
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;timedatectl status
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-bypass-check-testing-only"&gt;Fix 3: Bypass check (testing only)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SSL_CTX_set_verify&lt;/span&gt;(ctx, SSL_VERIFY_NONE, NULL); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// NOT for production
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check certificate expiry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;openssl s_client -connect example.com:443 &amp;lt;/dev/null 2&amp;gt;/dev/null | &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; openssl x509 -noout -dates
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check local certificate&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;openssl x509 -in cert.pem -noout -dates
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/tls-handshake-failure/"&gt;TLS handshake failure&lt;/a&gt; — general TLS error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/certificate-revoked/"&gt;Certificate revoked&lt;/a&gt; — revoked certificate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/hostname-mismatch/"&gt;Hostname mismatch&lt;/a&gt; — hostname error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_weak_ptr - expired weak_ptr</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-weak-ptr/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-weak-ptr/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdbad_weak_ptr---expired-weak_ptr"&gt;std::bad_weak_ptr - expired weak_ptr&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::bad_weak_ptr&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a &lt;code&gt;std::weak_ptr&lt;/code&gt; that has expired is used in contexts that require a valid &lt;code&gt;shared_ptr&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Expired weak_ptr
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;weak_ptr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; wp;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;{
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt; sp &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;make_shared&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; wp &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; sp;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// sp destroyed, wp expired
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt; sp &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; wp.lock(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// sp is nullptr
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Using expired pointer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;weak_ptr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; wp;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ... wp expires ...
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;shared_ptr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; sp &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; wp.lock(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// returns nullptr
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;sp; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// undefined behavior (dereferencing null)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: make_shared_from_this after destruction
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Obj&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;enable_shared_from_this&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Obj&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;shared_ptr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Obj&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; get_self() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;shared_from_this&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws if not managed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-lock-result"&gt;Fix 1: Check lock() result&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;shared_ptr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; sp &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; wp.lock();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (sp) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;sp;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-expired"&gt;Fix 2: Check expired()&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;wp.expired()) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt; sp &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; wp.lock();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-shared_from_this-safely"&gt;Fix 3: Use shared_from_this safely&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Obj&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;enable_shared_from_this&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Obj&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;shared_ptr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Obj&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; get_self() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;shared_from_this&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;bad_weak_ptr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nullptr&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-function-call/"&gt;std::bad_function_call&lt;/a&gt; — empty function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-optional-access/"&gt;std::bad_optional_access&lt;/a&gt; — empty optional.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-exception/"&gt;std::bad_exception&lt;/a&gt; — unexpected exception.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::weak_ptr Expired — Expired Weak Pointer Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/weak-ptr-expired/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/weak-ptr-expired/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdweak_ptr-expired--expired-weak-pointer-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::weak_ptr Expired — Expired Weak Pointer Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::weak_ptr&lt;/code&gt; becomes expired when all &lt;code&gt;std::shared_ptr&lt;/code&gt; instances managing the object have been destroyed. Calling &lt;code&gt;lock()&lt;/code&gt; returns nullptr, and attempting to access the object through an expired &lt;code&gt;weak_ptr&lt;/code&gt; without checking leads to null pointer dereferences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-weak_ptr-expired-occurs"&gt;Why weak_ptr Expired Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include the last &lt;code&gt;shared_ptr&lt;/code&gt; to the object being destroyed, holding a &lt;code&gt;weak_ptr&lt;/code&gt; beyond the managed object&amp;rsquo;s lifetime, race conditions where one thread destroys the last &lt;code&gt;shared_ptr&lt;/code&gt; while another accesses via &lt;code&gt;weak_ptr&lt;/code&gt;, and forgetting to check &lt;code&gt;lock()&lt;/code&gt; result.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] JsonWebTokenError: invalid signature Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/jsonwebtoken-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/jsonwebtoken-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="jsonwebtokenerror--invalid-signature"&gt;JsonWebTokenError — invalid signature&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when JWT token verification fails due to signature mismatch, expired token, or malformed token format.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common error messages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;JsonWebTokenError: invalid signature&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;TokenExpiredError: jwt expired&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;JsonWebTokenError: jwt malformed&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JWT tokens have three parts: header, payload, and signature. Verification fails when the signature doesn&amp;rsquo;t match the payload using the provided secret.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Wrong secret/key
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;token&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;jwt&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sign&lt;/span&gt;({ &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; }, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;secret-key&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
